cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.CR, cs.DS 

This paper is about monitoring distributed systems using behavioural contracts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also introduces a new process calculus for reasoning about monitoring of distributed systems, which suggests cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of fault-tolerance, which is a topic in cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also mentions communication overheads and computation load balancing, which are topics in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) respectively.
